                                    Working with code is challenging and satisfying and the complexity and diversity of outcomes is truly captivating.  
                                    Throughout my lifetime, I’ve been fortunate to witness firsthand the impact that software has had on our world.  
                                    I feel fortunate to be part of this evolving landscape.
                                    </p>
                                <ul class="social-share-transparent size-md">
                                    <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100005064616174"><i class="fab fa-facebook-f"></i></a></li>
@*                                     <li><a href="#"><i class="fab fa-instagram"></i></a></li>
                                    <li><a href="#"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li> *@
                                    <li><a asp-action="ContactMe" asp-controller="BlogPosts"><i class="far fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                    <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomas-j-farrell-jr-75195a94"><i class="fab fa-linkedin-in"></i></a></li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
